column1: Cases and hospitalizations are spiking in Iowa.  Businesses say they're on the brink.  More federal #COVID19 protections expire on January 1st.  Additional aid can't wait until 2021.  #IA03  https://t.co/gn7THuHJga

From natural disasters to the ongoing #COVID19 crisis Iowans have been through so much these past 2 years.  We have our work cut out for us – but I’m confident that we can pull together to overcome these challenges and build a brighter future for all.  #IA03 https://t.co/NsbAC6XH5D

Iowa's restaurants & service industry have been hit particularly hard by #COVID19.  As a small business owner I know how important it is to protect these community cornerstones – and I've fought for tangible relief to help keep their doors open.  #IA03 https://t.co/RbdNoy9I0m

With so many of our child care facilities closed down by #COVID19 we should recognize how central this infrastructure is to our communities & the larger economy.  Thanks for having me @SCActionNetwork! https://t.co/E06iWe5dEu

Maybe instead of laughing at campaigns taking #COVID19 seriously the Governor should be answering some questions herself. Here's one:   Are new records for hospitalizations and cases (2500 in a day!) going to change your mind on ignoring CDC/White House recommendations? https://t.co/sA9u8hUBUE

From multiple natural disasters to the brutal effects of #COVID19 – families in #IA03 have been through so much in the past 2 years.  And we've still got a ways to go.  But I’m proud that no matter what Iowans pull together and find a way forward.  📺 Watch our final ad: ⤵️ https://t.co/RpoRbJHHBH

With hospitalizations for #COVID19 in Iowa setting new records access to quality affordable health care has to be a priority during this crisis.  The future of our health care is on the ballot in #IA03. https://t.co/tno1iA96s0

Thousands of new #COVID19 cases a day.  The future of our health care system headed for the Supreme Court.  This is why Iowans tell me that health care is the #1 issue in this election.  #IA03 https://t.co/hirVqXZlhl

The economic fallout from the #COVID19 crisis has forced many Iowa families to make tough financial choices amidst job losses & widespread uncertainty.  I promise to keep fighting in Washington to deliver assistance for Iowans still in need.  #IA03 https://t.co/U8YQq5ZfhJ
With rising numbers of #COVID19 cases in Iowa & across the country access to quality affordable health care has to be a priority during this pandemic.  #IA03 https://t.co/YWC3JrXry0

These staggering case counts in Iowa are a reminder that #COVID19 hasn’t left our state.  It also shows us that now – more than ever – all Iowans need access to quality affordable health care.   #IA03  https://t.co/NRfgPC0bAw

Cindy is a small business owner & a champion for Iowa’s businesses and workers.  "[Cindy Axne's] continued leadership in Congress will benefit the nation as we combat the coronavirus work to restore economic growth & expand opportunities for all Americans." - @USChamber #IA03 https://t.co/JfDGL94d9m

Cindy Axne has been pushing for a simplified compromise #COVID19 package for months – and has been urging congressional leaders to meet in the middle to deliver aid for #IA03.  https://t.co/IifRoWHBO2

Over my first term folks in #IA03’s rural communities have faced #COVID19 a trade war historic floods & a derecho.  I will work with both parties to support those affected by these crises to improve the lives of rural Iowans. ⤵️ https://t.co/jDqwr3kNiQ https://t.co/YmjyZmbAVl

Between a derecho trade war and the economic issues exacerbated by #COVID19 our farmers & rural families have been through a lot these past 2 years.  Thank you @DSMpartnership for letting me talk about the importance of having farmers' backs in #IA03. https://t.co/o9QtAzJmHa

The challenges brought on by #COVID19 aren't over in Iowa.  Today – and everyday – we need to make sure we're doing everything we can to keep our families & communities safe.  #IA03 https://t.co/U3oqxQ1hJB

I’ve fought for Iowans through the crises that we have faced over these past two years.  From flooding and the trade war to #COVID19 – I’ve worked across the aisle and stood up to my own party when needed – and always put Iowa first.  #IA03 https://t.co/KGG062vHJX

Here's what the @USChamber told Cindy when they endorsed her: "you continued leadership in Congress will benefit the nation as we combat the coronavirus work to restore economic growth and expand opportunities for all Americans."  https://t.co/gKoC0UHMq8

FACT CHECK: True  For months Cindy has pushed congressional leadership and the White House to meet in the middle on a compromise package that could deliver aid for Iowans and help combat #COVID19.  #IA03  https://t.co/IifRoWHBO2
FACT CHECK: True  Cindy Axne has been fighting for months to protect Iowa's most vulnerable - our senior citizens - from coronavirus.  #IA03  https://t.co/0RYxOqbAU6

As we continue responding to #COVID19 & its economic fallout this is the WORST POSSIBLE MOMENT to gut critical health care protections.  We can’t afford to turn our backs on our seniors pregnant mothers and families still facing this crisis.  #IA03 https://t.co/GW43BwhVHv

As #COVID19 continues to spread in Iowa refusing to budge on additional relief won't help the families & communities still in need.   After pushing for a revised aid package we're closer than we've been in months – and we need to reach a deal ASAP. #IA03 https://t.co/kSkFEBwVd0 https://t.co/3i0D4EscxW

As we all wish the President and First Lady a full and fast recovery from #COVID19 - we must see this is a reminder that this virus can affect anyone.  It takes all of us following the advice of our medical experts to slow the spread of this disease. #IA03 https://t.co/qetpZxmKUc

Health care was the #1 issue in our last election – now w/ #COVID19 and vital protections (like for preex conditions) still at risk 2020 is no different.  I don’t just promise to protect Iowans’ care I vote to do so – and have fought to lower those costs for Iowa families.#IA03 https://t.co/sQIa13f0Jm

The persistence of #COVID19 in our communities is a reminder of how important access to health care is for Iowa’s families.  I am committed to expanding access to affordable quality health care and to supporting our hospitals & health clinics.  #IA03 https://t.co/VXKZsQoCdA

Rebuilding our economy amid the #COVID19 crisis shouldn’t be about tax breaks for big corporations – or cutting Medicare & Social Security benefits.  It should be about putting Iowa’s middle-class families first.  #IA03 https://t.co/VTdqN0iLR6

Now – in the middle of a global pandemic and economic crisis – is the worst possible moment to put millions of Americans’ health care at risk by repealing the ACA.  We need to build on & expand its protections as #IA03 grapples w/ the effects of #COVID19. https://t.co/RqpGPV4sYm

We also need to keep working to expand and keep telemedicine available for those hit hardest by #COVID19.  Together we can make sure every Iowan gets the care they deserve. Will you join me in this fight #IA03? (3/3)⬇️ https://t.co/5odWZu8p7h

3 of every 5 child care facilities have closed from #COVID19 – and many report their closures may be permanent.  If we don't directly address the looming child care crisis millions of working families will be left behind & we won't be able to get our economy back on track. #IA03 https://t.co/iV7DgZgmn9

While I’d love to be out shaking hands giving hugs & high-fives – and filling our rally halls – #COVID19 has meant campaigning looks a little different this year.  Proud of @polkdems for showing that we can still organize without putting Iowans at risk.👍 https://t.co/LvBwu34PDd

Our schools small businesses and health services are still under immense pressure from #COVID19.  Folks need help to ensure they can keep a roof over their heads and food on their table.  We need less partisan games and more action.  #IA03   https://t.co/Ij8bsAEpyJ

The tragic loss of one of @DMschools' dedicated educators is a sobering reminder of the risks facing our schools & communities.  We need to allow districts to make decisions that will best protect their students and staff from the spread of #COVID19. #IA03 https://t.co/qR3KbgdzIj

Last week Iowa was reporting over 1000 positive cases a day – and we're at the top of the list nationally.   Now is not the time to let your guard down on #COVID19!  😷 Wear a mask  🧍‍♀️➖🧍‍♂️Follow socially distancing   🏡 Minimize exposure to others  #IA03 https://t.co/iqXzDlJrdq

This crisis is far from over in Iowa.  #COVID19 case counts are hitting new records.  Unemployment claims are climbing again and we're having to re-close businesses to slow the spread.  I will not accept a stalemate in Washington over additional aid.#IA03 https://t.co/wed482qzmJ

Iowa's housing advocates saying loud & clear that #COVID19 is going to make Iowa's housing challenges more difficult.  Not only do we need to protect Iowans from losing their homes we need federal investments to expand access to affordable housing. #IA03  https://t.co/oWW6EUUlXQ

Thousands of Iowans are still:  ❌ out of work  ❌ struggling to keep food on their table  ❌ worried about sending their kids back to school  ❌ unsure how to make rent on Sept. 1  Political stalemate on additional #COVID19 relief is not an option. #IA03  https://t.co/nKF99foeEy https://t.co/rQZOXQnlMn

Getting through now that's the problem. That's the day-to-day battle.  That's how 5th generation #IA03 farmer Dan Ryner summed up the effects of a devastating trade war uncertain markets & #COVID19.  📺 Watch our conversation from last night's @DemConvention segment. #IA03 ⤵️ https://t.co/WFFYzql9yj

Iowa families have been facing difficult financial times during #COVID19 threatening their ability to keep food on their tables and roof over their heads.  I'm proud of my work helping Iowans in these tough times and I'm pleased to share the story of one such #IA03 family: https://t.co/r5SC7QuRNz

Businesses that rely on Iowa's biggest events of the year like the State Fair or RAGBRAI are facing losses from #COVID19 that could devastate local #IA03 economies.  Measures like the RESTART Act could help them through specific aid to keep them afloat. https://t.co/jsl3eS6ERO

I’m glad I could join the Iowa Alliance for Retired Americans @ProtectOurCare @IowaVoices @afscme_c61 and @ProgressIowa for a Town Hall on the need to protect our seniors and those in care centers from Coronavirus. https://t.co/0p8AAlitAd

Polk and Dallas counties have begun to see an increase in positive COVID-19 cases. When we #WearAMask we are telling our friends and neighbors that we care about their health and safety. I urge all Iowans to practice social distancing and #WearAMask when they leave their home. https://t.co/RXhMNlWXFo

Because of the Affordable Care Act 20 million additional Americans gained quality affordable health care. Now more than ever we need to build on that and give uninsured Americans the opportunity to get insured under a special enrollment period for COVID-19. Enough. #TeamJoe
